  <mainDescription>&lt;a id=&quot;Top&quot; name=&quot;Top&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Overview&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The following is a summary of steps that you perform to manage the Process View:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ol>&#xD;
    &lt;li class=&quot;mvd-P&quot;>&#xD;
        &lt;p>&#xD;
            &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
            href=&quot;./../../../core.base_rup/guidances/toolmentors/document_process_view_6026C17A.html&quot;&#xD;
            guid=&quot;{059DD277-2FC8-4977-836A-2EDAF219655F}&quot;>Create the &lt;b>&lt;span style=&quot;FONT-WEIGHT: normal&quot;>Process&#xD;
            View&lt;/span>&lt;/b> in the &lt;b>&lt;span style=&quot;FONT-WEIGHT: normal&quot;>Logical View&lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;/a>&#xD;
        &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li class=&quot;mvd-P&quot;>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../../core.base_rup/guidances/toolmentors/document_process_view_6026C17A.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{059DD277-2FC8-4977-836A-2EDAF219655F}&quot;>Represent processes using 'Active Classes' in the Process Model&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li class=&quot;mvd-P&quot;>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../../core.base_rup/guidances/toolmentors/document_process_view_6026C17A.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{059DD277-2FC8-4977-836A-2EDAF219655F}&quot;>Represent process and thread lifecycles&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li class=&quot;mvd-P&quot;>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../../core.base_rup/guidances/toolmentors/document_process_view_6026C17A.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{059DD277-2FC8-4977-836A-2EDAF219655F}&quot;>Allocate classes to processes and threads&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ol>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    1. &lt;a id=&quot;Creating the Process Model in the Rational Rose (TM) Logical View&quot;&#xD;
    name=&quot;Creating the Process Model in the Rational Rose (TM) Logical View&quot;>&lt;/a>Create the &lt;b>Process View&lt;/b> in the&#xD;
    &lt;b>Logical View&lt;/b> &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../core.base_rup/guidances/toolmentors/document_process_view_6026C17A.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{059DD277-2FC8-4977-836A-2EDAF219655F}&quot;>&lt;img height=&quot;20&quot; alt=&quot;To top of page&quot; hspace=&quot;0&quot;&#xD;
    src=&quot;../../resources/top.gif&quot; width=&quot;26&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; />&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    You represent the Process View by creating a package within the Logical View and naming it &quot;Process View&quot;.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    2. &lt;a id=&quot;Representing Processes using 'Active Classes' in the Process Model&quot;&#xD;
    name=&quot;Representing Processes using 'Active Classes' in the Process Model&quot;>&lt;/a>Represent Processes Using 'Active&#xD;
    Classes' in the Process&amp;nbsp;&lt;br />&#xD;
     Model &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../core.base_rup/guidances/toolmentors/document_process_view_6026C17A.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{059DD277-2FC8-4977-836A-2EDAF219655F}&quot;>&lt;img height=&quot;20&quot; alt=&quot;To top of page&quot; hspace=&quot;0&quot;&#xD;
    src=&quot;../../resources/top.gif&quot; width=&quot;26&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; />&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The UML represents processes and threads as &lt;b>Active Classes&lt;/b> in the Process View. You create an active class in&#xD;
    the Process View by creating a class and assigning it a stereotype of either &amp;lt;process&amp;gt; or &amp;lt;thread&amp;gt;.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    3. &lt;a id=&quot;Representing Process and Thread Life-cycles&quot; name=&quot;Representing Process and Thread Life-cycles&quot;>&lt;/a>Represent&#xD;
    process and thread lifecycles &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../core.base_rup/guidances/toolmentors/document_process_view_6026C17A.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{059DD277-2FC8-4977-836A-2EDAF219655F}&quot;>&lt;img height=&quot;20&quot; alt=&quot;To top of page&quot; hspace=&quot;0&quot;&#xD;
    src=&quot;../../resources/top.gif&quot; width=&quot;26&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; />&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    You use Sequence Diagrams to represent process and thread lifecycles. Each process or thread should appear in the&#xD;
    sequence diagrams that create and destroy it. In addition, it is useful to illustrate complex inter-process and&#xD;
    inter-thread communication using additional sequence diagrams. These sequence diagrams should be organized with the Use&#xD;
    Case Realization in which the behavior occurs.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    When you create your sequence diagrams and the objects in them, consider a labeling convention where you show the&#xD;
    initiator of the first message as the interface itself.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;img height=&quot;16&quot; alt=&quot;helpbook icon&quot; hspace=&quot;0&quot; src=&quot;../../resources/helpbook.gif&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; /> For more&#xD;
    information about sequence diagrams, see the &lt;span style=&quot;FONT-STYLE: italic&quot;>Sequence Diagrams (Overview)&lt;/span> topic&#xD;
    in the Rational Rose online help.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    4. &lt;a id=&quot;Allocating Classes to Processes and Threads&quot;&#xD;
    name=&quot;Allocating Classes to Processes and Threads&quot;>&lt;/a>Allocating classes to processes and threads &lt;a&#xD;
    class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot; href=&quot;./../../../core.base_rup/guidances/toolmentors/document_process_view_6026C17A.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{059DD277-2FC8-4977-836A-2EDAF219655F}&quot;>&lt;img height=&quot;20&quot; alt=&quot;To top of page&quot; hspace=&quot;0&quot;&#xD;
    src=&quot;../../resources/top.gif&quot; width=&quot;26&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; />&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Classes and subsystems may be allocated to one or more processes and threads. Processes and threads are composed-of&#xD;
    instances of classes and subsystems. To show this allocation, you create class diagrams that model the processes and&#xD;
    threads as active classes. Use aggregation relationships to show the composition of the active classes. When you create&#xD;
    the aggregation relationships, use the Aggregation Specification to set the By Value containment for Role A.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
